SIMPLE: eldest
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eldest
<hw>Eld"est</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>yldest</ets>, superl. of <ets>eald</ets> old. See <er>Elder</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Oldest; longest in duration.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Born or living first, or before the others, as a
son, daughter, brother, etc.; first in origin. See <er>Elder</er>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧My lady's <xex>eldest</xex> son.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their <qex>eldest</qex> historians are of suspected credit.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Eldest hand</b></col> <fld>(Card Playing)</fld>, <cd>the
player on the dealer's left hand.</cd> <rj><au>R. A.
Proctor.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elding</ent>⟦br⟧
